Xinhua Review: Turning Outstanding Returning Migrant Workers into a New Force for Rural Revitalization
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
The outstanding group of returning migrant workers is an indispensable fresh force.
Xinhua News Agency, Shang Hai Spring
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26, Telegram Question: Turning Outstanding Returning Migrant Workers into a New Force for Rural Revitalization
The 34-year-old Zhang Xiong, whose family lives in Orchard Village in Meishan City, Sichuan, quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands of dollars to start a business in 2010.
After several years of struggle, now the grape-growing family farm he runs has an annual income of more than a million yuan, has become a well-known leader of wealth, and has also been selected into the team of the village "two committees".
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support and benefit farmers, such as the national fight against poverty and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in rural areas.
Sichuan, a province with a large population and a large labour export province in western China, has led the implementation of the "Return and Training Project for Outstanding Migrant Workers" due to favourable circumstances. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were produced from among the outstanding migrant workers returned, 61,000 village reserves were trained and more than 20,000 party members were developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Well-off is not well-off, the key is to look at the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged workers in rural China have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the emergence of "hollowing out" in rural areas to different degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations, and the ranks of village Party branch secretaries and Party members show the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, old age, low education, weak ranks of leaders of village Party organizations, and the lack of access to young and yellow.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing one way to the city, the countryside has long been in the state of "blood loss" and "anemia", revitalization is an empty word.
Attracting rural migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometown back, guiding them to return home and start their own businesses to become rich leaders, choosing their best to train them into Party members and rural cadres, and enriching the ranks of cadres at the grass-roots level, is the solution to the root cause of the problem of the lack of youth and yellow among rural Party members and grass-roots Party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers can be brought back, but also let them stay and do a good job.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the Party construction of rural migrant workers and, on the basis of strict candidate standards, has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted return, service guarantee, training and ability enhancement, selection and use of outstanding rural migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, secure their jobs and have expectations in their lives, truly take root in rural areas and have a sense of accomplishment in their entrepreneurship.
This year is the closing year of the decisive battle against poverty. Talents are the key factor in the connection between poverty eradication and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to this group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and adopt comprehensive measures to turn them into a task force and fresh force that can stay, fight and not take away, so as to provide strong organizational security and talent support for rural areas to lift themselves out of poverty and strive for a well-off, development and revitalization.
