Church Fire in Nantes, France: Parish Volunteers Admit to Arson
China News Network, July 26: On July 18, the famous St. Peter and St. Paul Cathedral, a treasure of religious and historical architecture in Nantes, France, was severely damaged in a fire and the cathedral organ was completely destroyed, foreign media reported.
On the 26th local time, the Nantes prosecutor announced that a parish volunteer responsible for guarding the cathedral had been charged with "arson and destruction".
He has admitted that he lit the fire in the church.
Local prosecutor Senas said the 39-year-old diocesan volunteer from Rwanda admitted to setting fires in three places in the middle of the cathedral at night.
The man's lawyer said the arsonist now regretted doing so.
This person entered France through the way of asylum a few years ago, was sheltered in the parish where the fire occurred, and was taken in in the church.
The prosecution pointed out that he had recently tried to renew his visa and was talking to the police about it.
But the church said it still could not believe that the normally very kind, smiling but not very talkative believer would destroy the church he loved so much.
On the day of the fire on July 18, the volunteer had already been questioned by the police for illogical problems in his account, but he was later released.
The picture shows firefighters rescuing at the scene.
On the evening of the 25th, he was summoned again as professional engineers at the laboratory of the Paris Central Police obtained new evidence.
This time, the man admitted to the arson.
It was reported that if convicted of arson and vandalism, the suspects could face 10 years in prison and a fine of 150,000 euros.
The report said the fire caused serious damage to the Cathedral of St. Pierre and St. Paul, where the organ was completely destroyed and the stained glass windows behind the organ were severely damaged.
According to Brunet, the chief architect of French historic preservation, it is conservatively estimated that the restoration of Nantes Cathedral will take at least three years.
Comprehensive news: US unilateralism undermines bilateral relations International public opinion supports China's countermeasures against the US - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26: On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the US Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the license for the establishment and operation of the US Consulate General in Chengdu, and made specific requests for the Consulate General to cease all operations and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious distress to China-US relations. It is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to the unreasonable provocations of the United States and take countermeasures.
Andrés Bolquez, Director of the Center for China Studies at the Institute of International Studies of the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have destroyed the bridge of understanding between the Chinese and American peoples and put the relations between the two major countries in crisis.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures of the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the Argentine Catholic University and director of the Center for Arab-China Studies, believes that the above-mentioned decision by China is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocations by the United States, not against the ordinary American people.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American public by pressuring China to cover up its inadequate response to the new epidemic.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said the provocative diplomatic posture adopted by the United States has caused serious distress to China-US relations and bilateral relations are facing serious challenges.
China's notification to the United States of the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure and is in line with diplomatic practice. It reflects both China's principled position of firmly safeguarding its own interests and the rational and beneficial nature of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the US provocation.
For China-US relations to return to normal, the US should take the initiative to improve its relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve win-win results with China economically and politically, and how to benefit the two peoples and even the international community as a whole.
Ali Youssef, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures China was forced to take were a legitimate and necessary response to the unjustified actions of the United States and were in line with international law and the basic norms governing international relations, as well as with diplomatic practices.
Earlier, the United States called for the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, a serious violation of international law and the basic norms governing international relations.
We hope that the US will rescind its previous relevant decisions and create the necessary conditions for bilateral relations to return to normalcy.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao published an editorial saying that the larger strategic intention of the United States is to encircle China and prevent its continued rise.
In the face of the pressing steps of the United States, although China is very reluctant to see China-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
