Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, July 26 (Guo Dongming, Xiong Liang) The Recruitment Office of the Jiangxi Provincial People's Government has recently made it clear that priority will be given to the recruitment of individuals or their children who have shown outstanding performance in the flood rescue and relief mission, who meet the recruitment conditions and who have passed both medical and political examinations.
"After the enlistment of young people is registered, we will give priority to the enlistment of young people after verification by the communities where the enlistment is located, the Street Armed Forces Department and the Luoyang District Recruitment Office."
Wang Hui, Vice Minister of People and Military Affairs of Luoyang District of Jiujiang City, said that affected by the floods, they focused three days on organizing medical check-ups for young applicants from the 25th.
Zhou Jingfan is a 22-year-old college graduate. His mother is a community worker and his father is a retired veteran of a department of the Air Force. Zhou's parents have been on the front line of flood prevention and control for the past 10 days.
"These days, seeing in the news that the people's children and soldiers are desperate to defend their hometown on the anti-flood front, I also want to be like them."
Zhou said he had a dream of joining the army since he was a child, and the fight against the floods strengthened his determination to join the military camp.
Jiujiang City has also taken anti-flood and rescue as a "living teaching material" for conscription propaganda. Taking the community as a unit, they called on the young conscripts to voluntarily take part in the tasks of patrolling the embankment and on duty. They now understand the nature and purpose of the people's army and strengthen their confidence in joining the army and serving the country.
Luo Jiuyu, political commissar of the People's Military Department of Luoyang District of Jiujiang City, said that by giving priority to the recruitment of soldiers, he hopes to inspire more young conscripts and create a good social atmosphere in which it is glorious to take part in the mission and join the army.
