The upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship Ka-52M was first produced at the end of the year.
MOSCOW, July 25, 2020 / PRNewswire / -- According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the upgraded version of the Ka-52M of the Russian helicopter gunship (hereinafter referred to as the Wu-Zhong) Ka-52 will be upgraded and replaced for the first time in December this year. The aircraft will be significantly improved in reconnaissance, communication and weapon performance.
The contract for the development of the Wuzhika-52M, called "Super Alligator," was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year. At present, the first two upgraded versions of the Wuzhika-52M are being modified and replaced at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of the Russian "Progressive" Aerospace Group, and the completion of its national-level testing and improvement will be completed by October 2022, the Russian Yediot reported recently.
According to Russian experts familiar with the above-mentioned upgrading work, the "predecessor" of the "Super Alligator", the Kun-Wuzhika-52, was officially installed in November 2011, and some weaknesses were exposed in the use of the model, which was upgraded to "make up for the short plate".
