"Putting on the Jiangnan" and Pursuing the Poetic "Dream of the Yellow River"
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) The Search for Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Agency Yinchuan July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River thousands of miles of sand, the waves from the Tianya."
The Yellow River, which aroused the pride of countless literati Chizi Wanzhang, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Now, Ningxia, which is known as "Putting on the Jiangnan", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River dream".
"Blue Wave Dream" of River Clear Water Show
"The world's Yellow River is rich in Ningxia", and the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, which is the "mother river" of raising one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are unbalanced, and chaotic images such as exceeding the standards for sewage discharge, encircling lakes for land and encroaching on water areas have emerged, leading to the black odor of water bodies, exceeding the standards for water quality, environmental mess and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and working hard to return the Xiuhe Qing of the Yellow River.
Treat water from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local method of "raising the bid + controlling pollution + strict management" was adopted, all sewage from industrial parks was centrally treated, all urban sewage treatment plants achieved Grade I A standard discharge, black and smelly water bodies were basically eliminated in urban built-up areas, and the third batch of Chinese black and smelly water demonstration cities was successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the long-term river and lake system in 2017, and has now achieved full coverage of the five-level long-term river and lake responsibility system in districts, cities and counties and villages, and long river and lake patrols have become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village on the edge of the Yellow River, witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: "The water used to have a bad smell, and the smell has disappeared after remediation."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often walks along the Yellow River with his family to feel the clear water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Sha Luoxiang Collection
Flying birds, green trees, trestle roads, clear water.. Fan Zhongyan wrote that the beautiful scenery of "sand and informative collection" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
As the Yellow River flows through Ningxia, a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands have been formed along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance, and has also become an important international migration channel for birds.
Since 2009, the relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of about RMB 3.45 billion in wetland protection projects. At present, the area of Yinchuan wetlands is 19.2 million hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5 per cent. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, with five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six autonomous region-level wetland parks and eight municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. "The remaining gull is an endangered bird, with only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in the Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has demarcated the red line of the 500-meter zone for the protection area of wetlands on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the protection area except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the control of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of the ecology of rivers and lakes and the construction of end wetlands, the water quality of the nine main yellow drains in Ningxia has now reached 100% of the standards. "Now the water is also clear, the fish swim and the flowers bloom."
Pu Huimin's "Drinking Water Dream"
Ningxia Yinchuan City once had an "awkward" title: the only city along the Yellow River that "guards the Yellow River for water and drinking".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been faced with a persistent problem of water shortage at the peak of summer, and the "pain of water shortage" in the past decade has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, with the fact that major water sources are at the limit of overmining and a large area of groundwater overmining funnel area has been formed underground in the city, the water shortage has become a difficult problem perplexing Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking the purified Yellow River has become a good solution to the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, Deputy Director of the Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water needs of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia launched the Yinchuan Metropolitan Area Urban and Rural Western Line Water Supply Project in a timely manner, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially opened water to the three districts of Yinchuan City, and in 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said the Yinchuan water conservancy department will give overall consideration to the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. "As a next step, we will integrate all the decentralized rural water supply points into the Western Line water supply project, and it is expected that the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan region will basically be realized by the end of this year."
