Shenzhen Public Consultation on Issuing Health Regulations
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporter Mao Siqian, Bai Yu) encourages residents to do medical check-ups diligently to detect problems as early as possible; prohibits the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establishes an online game health review system; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health managers... Recently, the Regulations on Health in the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone (Consultation Draft) were officially issued, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to do frequent medical check-ups and detect problems as early as possible, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health check-ups according to different age, occupation and other factors.
The health check-up expenses that fall within the scope of the basic catalogue of health check-up items shall be paid by the Social Medical Insurance Co-ordinating Fund at the rate of once per person per year.
The consultation draft makes it clear that the employing units shall rationally allocate human resources, arrange employees' working and rest hours, implement a rotation rest system for employees with heavy mental and physical labour loads, so as to avoid excessive loss of human function or injury to the health of the employees, and strictly implement the paid leave system for employees.
In addition, employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health managers and organize regular health check-ups for employees.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the consultation draft proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, while the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages is restricted. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "prohibition of alcohol", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the consultation draft, schools should arrange students' sports activities for more than one hour a day.
With regard to online games, the departments of public security, cultural, radio and television tourism and sports, network supervision, health and health should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business places, establish an online game health review system, and create a good communication space and communication culture for the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the consultation draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and that medical and health institutions be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the consultation draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of the implementation of public policies on the health of the population before formulating plans and normative documents relating to urban spatial planning and construction, the planning and construction of industrial parks, the exploitation and utilization of resources and ecological environmental protection, and the development of the biomedical industry, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
Where it has not been evaluated or will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents, it shall not be formulated, promulgated or approved for implementation.
