Experts suggest that when going out in summer, it is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon, because the sun is strongest during this time, the likelihood of heatstroke is higher.
If you have to go out at this time, you must do a good job of protection, such as playing a sunshade, wearing a sunshade hat, wearing sunglasses, the best conditions to apply sunscreen to prevent sunburn.
