Xinhua News Agency Kuala Lumpur, July 25 (reporter Lin Hao) The trade ministers of members of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) held a videoconference on July 25, at which they pledged to work to reduce the impact of the new epidemic on the regional economy and accelerate the achievement of a resilient, sustainable and inclusive regional economic recovery.
The meeting was hosted by Malaysia, the host of this year's APEC Leaders' Informal Meeting.
