Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan Zhang Shushan Xu Jingyi) China's famous vascular surgery center, Shanghai Changhai Hospital Vascular Surgery, Shanghai-Naval Military Medical University, signed a contract with Zhongshan Hospital Vascular Surgery, affiliated with Xiamen University, on July 25 to jointly set up a collaboration center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially aortic emergency and severe disease.
The Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, said that after the vascular surgery of the two hospitals formally formed a collaborative unit, it will conduct remote consultations, formulate treatment plans with real-time online consultations with Changhai Hospital, select and send talents for further training, and jointly carry out weekly surgical technical exchanges, teaching room inspections, etc. For complex cases, experts from Changhai can be invited to the hospital to perform operations according to the needs of the patients, thus realizing that patients in southwest Fujian Province can enjoy the country's top medical resources.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative surgical scientific research, popular science and early screening of aortic diseases, etc.
A special seminar on the aorta organized by the Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by the Zhongshan Hospital attached to Xiamen University was held in Xiamen on the same day.
At the same time, the two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Xiamen held the signing ceremony of the vascular surgery collaboration center and announced the formation of collaborative units to jointly improve the treatment level of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
Shanghai Changhai Hospital Vascular Surgery is the only Institute of Vascular Surgery in the Army and the only Clinical Medical Center for Vascular System Diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline in vascular surgery. It has led the establishment of the Intraperitoneal Angiology Professional Committee of the Chinese Physicians Association, and is a top team with a deep history in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, gave an interview to the media.
Vascular surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is the first independent subject of vascular surgery in Fujian Province. It has long been dedicated to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases, and was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty in 2018.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissection aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, there is extensive experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
"The history of vascular surgery in Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University and the breadth, difficulty and complexity of the operation are outstanding in the region, so this time we set up a collaboration center to carry out in-depth cooperation in the diagnosis and treatment of diseases such as lower extremity artery and carotid artery in addition to the aorta."
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital affiliated with Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract to establish "Li Zhaoshen Famous Medical Studio" in digestive medicine in 2018.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of vascular surgery at the hospital, told CNN.com that the hospital also has a long history of exchanges with Changhai Hospital.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to the hospital to carry out surgical technical exchanges, teaching room visits, discussion of difficult cases, and further carry out remote consultations, which are currently planned to be held once a week. In addition, the department will also send personnel for further study exchanges to strengthen the training and development of the contingent of talents in the subject.
At the meeting, the reporter learned that vascular diseases are the leading cause of death in China. The aorta, as the main channel of all organs of the human body, flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic diseases is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty of treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is up to 4 cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, there is a rupture, or the rupture of the intima produces a dissection, which will cause heavy bleeding and is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyle and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the largest country in the world with hypertension, and aortic diseases have increased. Today, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases has continued to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can achieve good results by piercing the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta to properly "change the channel" of blood flow, thus avoiding the impact of an aneurysm or ruptured dissection, and some operations even require only local anesthesia.
More than a dozen domestic experts were invited to attend the seminar to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and the cutting-edge technical training and discussion of difficult cases were carried out in the form of a conference salon.
At the meeting, the reporter learned that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
