The longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Responsible Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Xiao Three Gorges Tunnel.
Map supplied by China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group
China News Network Chongqing July 26 (reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Limited on July 26 that the 18.9-kilometer-long Zheng Wan High-Speed Rail Little Three Gorges Tunnel ran through the entire line on that day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole two-line high-speed rail tunnel designed to reach a speed of 350 km / h in China.
Located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing, the Zheng Wan High-Speed Railway connects Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan High-Speed Railway in Zhengzhou to the north, and the South-Lien-Yuwan High-Speed Railway in Wanzhou to Chongqing. It is an important part of the "eight-vertical and eight-horizontal" high-speed railway network in China.
The entire line of the Zheng Wan High-Speed Rail Xiao Three Gorges Tunnel opened on the 26th.
The picture shows the through site.
The Zheng Wan high-speed railway begins in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Xiangyang City, Hubei Province, to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City. The new line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou to Xiangyang section was first opened for operation on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up its construction.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the whole line on the 26th, is the full-line control project of Zheng Wan High-Speed Rail. The project is located at the border between Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing. It is about 18.9 kilometers long and has a maximum burial depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and the entire line opened on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Jun, who is in charge of high-speed railway tunnel design of Zheng Wan Engineering Group of China Railway Second Academy of Engineering, the survey and design party, the Xiao Three Gorges Tunnel is located in a very complex terrain and geological condition, facing the risks of karst, mud inrush water and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Grade I high-risk tunnel, and the tunnel design and construction are very difficult.
"In the course of the construction of the project, we used the methods of geological investigation, geophysical exploration and advanced drilling to advance geological prediction, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 caverns of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built, crossing a large cavern with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement," the Royal Army said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction party, the construction of the tunnel adopted the combination of diversion and blocking, through the construction of cross-hole leveling, grouting to block water, the strengthening of tunnel structural support and the construction of sewage treatment station, which not only ensured the orderly progress of the project, but also avoided the damage of the construction drainage to the water body in the Xiaotangxia Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcome construction difficulties such as bad geology such as the large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long, and multi-inrush water with a maximum daily water inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
After the completion and opening to traffic, the entire line of Zheng Wan high-speed railway will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport route from the southwest of China to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast-to-northeast railway corridor in the southwest, improve the layout of the regional road network, accelerate the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote coordinated regional development and promote the implementation of the strategy for the development of the western region.
