In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China made overall efforts to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The situation of epidemic prevention and control continued to improve, the steady economic recovery was evident, the performance of employment and prices, which are closely related to the people's livelihood, was generally stable, and the Chinese economy handed over a report card of warm economic operation.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate rose.
In particular, in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically shut down and shut down, the demand for employment by enterprises was reduced, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the unemployment rate in urban surveys rose.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the order of production and life of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of seeking progress in stability, further strengthens the hedging of macroeconomic policies, comprehensively strengthens the priority employment policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting enterprises to stabilize jobs and expand employment.
China has increased its policy to hedge and stabilize jobs, played a policy combination of "relief, relief and slow return compensation", reduced and reduced the payment portion of three social insurance units in stages, allowed the postponement of the payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of unemployment insurance stabilization and job return for small and medium-sized and micro-enterprises, and provided absorption subsidies and internship subsidies to enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the detailed implementation of various stable employment policies, the demand for employment by enterprises has steadily recovered, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the urban survey unemployment rate has gradually declined. In June, the survey unemployment rate was 5.7 per cent.
Zhang Yi, Director of the Department of Population and Employment Statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to bear fruit, with the labor force that had withdrawn in the previous period due to the impact of the epidemic returning, and the urban labor force participation rate rose by about 10 percentage points in June compared with February, close to the level of the same period last year.
Data show that the total amount of urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached pre-epidemic levels; the average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices also concern thousands of families.
In January this year, the CPI rose 5.4% year-on-year, a multi-year high.
Entering February, the CPI year-on-year increase, although slightly reduced, is still in the "5 range."
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, not only the consumer demand-driven factors before the Spring Festival, but also the wrong month of the Spring Festival and the low year-on-year base factors.
However, the impact of the new pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly evident.
Affected by the epidemic prevention and control, in January and February, all parts of the country experienced delays in logistics, untimely supply of materials and materials, and increased transport costs of materials, as well as hoarding and panic-buying by some citizens, resulting in a marked increase in the prices of some necessities of life.
In order to deal with the disturbance of the price situation caused by the prevention and control of the epidemic, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the emergency transport guarantee to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the influence of a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables, melons and fruits has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the Central Government introduced the policy of guaranteeing supply and stabilizing prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, the supply of pork reserves improved significantly, pig production capacity was restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and marketing was gradually normal.
Since March, pork prices have fallen continuously, and the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6 per cent in May. In June, pork prices rose slightly on an annualized basis, influenced by factors such as the slowdown in the export of pigs, the reduction in the volume of imports and the rebound in group consumer demand.
The seasonal variation of fresh vegetable prices was obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high comparative base in the same period last year, fresh fruit prices continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decrease of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the people is effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation is stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, all places have increased the strength of guarantee and supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Beginning in March, the CPI ring-to-ring ratio declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase fell from 4.3 per cent in March to 2.5 per cent in June, and the overall price level returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level and the overall inflationary pressure will not be great, but we should still promote the restoration of the order of production and life on the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
We will effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods, droughts and other natural disasters in major producing areas of grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on acts that disrupt market order such as hoarding and inflating prices.
