Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect"
Diagram of Preparation Technology of New Hybrid Matrix Film
This newspaper reporter Shang Rui reported: Recently, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University has made significant progress in "carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation method", successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology, and greatly improved the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
The results have been published as a cover article in the international journal Greenhouse Gases: Science and Technology.
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem perplexing human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit of the "greenhouse effect".
How to capture and utilize human carbon dioxide efficiently is the focus of scientists' attention.
"Membrane separation method" is a new carbon dioxide capture technology. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials, which has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to make membrane materials "breathe deeply" and improve the efficiency of gas separation is the bottleneck and difficulty of capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation method.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University has an innovative idea to explore the influence of different solvents on the gas separation performance of films through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that the carbon nanotubes produced by N-methylpyrrolidone are more evenly distributed and "more breathable" in the membrane material, effectively improving the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of mixed matrix films prepared by this new technology is close to the theoretical separation limit of this kind of membrane materials.
"The new technology provides a new idea for capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation."
