Find out what professional grade difference is before you volunteer.
2020-07-27 02: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Responsible Editor: Yu Xiao
Find out what professional grade is before you volunteer
Every year, there are students or parents who volunteer for the college entrance examination because they do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary application, which affects the voluntary application.
This year, five colleges and universities, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing Chemical University, jointly issued enrollment policies for 2020, eliminating professional grade differences.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference and what is the significance in voluntary filing?
There are three ways to assign professional rules
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteer, it is important to read the "Admission Charter" of the desired school and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the transfer ratio, the rules of professional allocation, etc.
The rules of professional allocation refer to the three ways of professional priority, score priority and professional grade difference for professional admission after the transfer of colleges and universities.
The specific way used by colleges and universities will be made clear in the Admission Charter.
But there are also some colleges and universities whose admission principle is to give priority to the total score, and there is no grade difference between the majors.
That is, the candidates within the admission range will be lined up according to the total score, when the score does not reach the voluntary admission score for the first major, it will see whether the voluntary admission score for the second major has been reached, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, and there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" means that, when arranging candidates' majors, institutions determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates for different majors according to one or more score values published in the admission regulations. This score value is "professional grade difference".
This is the score difference between the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer in the admission of candidates, and the grade difference between the various professional volunteers, such as 3, 2, 1, etc.
Take for example.
Suppose the student Xiaoming applied for the examination of A university and scored 560 points, and his professional volunteers were: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce. The professional admission of A university implemented the method of professional grade difference, which was divided into 2, 1, 1 and 0 points.
In the professional assignment, if Xiaoming's first major volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming will be admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not accepted, his score will be reduced by 2 points, according to the ranking of 558 points with the candidates who volunteer for the "international trade" examination in the first major, to determine whether they meet the professional admission conditions; if the score is still not met, the score will be reduced by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for the admission of the fourth major, and so on.
Different professional grade difference settings in different universities
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now abolished professional grade differentials, but some colleges and universities have still retained this method this year. According to the Admission Charter published by various schools, more than 20 universities have mainly set up professional grade differentials this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Institute, etc.
In these colleges and universities, the professional grades set by each university are different.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences in each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates whose files have been submitted to the university are admitted by grade after decreasing one point in the order in which the candidates fill in their professional volunteers.
Some universities have set different professional grades between different majors.
In Jimei University, for example, the total difference between professional volunteers is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points, there is no difference between other professional volunteers, which is considered as a parallel volunteer, and the difference between other professional volunteers and professional volunteers is 1 point.
When applying for volunteers, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is a professional grade difference and what the form of the grade difference is. While giving full consideration to the score, they should also make a reasonable analysis of the schools and majors to be selected. If the institution clearly adopts the method of score difference in its admission charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the various majors when choosing a major to improve the admission probability.
