At present, the Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
"Now, as soon as you get out of the house, you enter the factory door and make money and take care of the family, thanks to the free vocational skills training of the trade union organization," said Lu Ling, an employee of the Kunming Esford Electronic Technology Company.
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop of electronic component processing in the copper capital of Dongchuan District, a busy picture of heat came into view.
In her 40s, Lu Ling is a single mother who takes care of her elderly parents.
In her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to come up with ideas and ways to "send money in the snow" after being busy before running.
Since 2018, Lu Ling has benefited from assistance policies such as housing, schooling, social security and employment, as well as assistance grants from trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and been employed, and she herself has a job and income after attending skills training, and was out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the special skills training project of the Dongchuan District General Organization to help fight poverty is part of the skills training work of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions.
Taking into account the characteristics of the difficult workers in the poverty alleviation relocation and resettlement sites in the area, the district will conduct an in-depth investigation to understand the training needs and determine the types of training, and plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders and noodle artists in the near future.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Menglian County Branch of the Agricultural Bank of Yunnan, wrote a sincere thank-you letter to the County General Trade Union.
In her letter, she expressed her sincere gratitude to the union for the grant she received from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the file of workers in difficulty. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the policy of building a file card.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed his studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantees and precise assistance.
The successful relief of the Lu Ling family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the work of Yunnan trade unions to promote the relief and relief of workers in difficulty.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Human Rights Work Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the province has always strengthened the dynamic management of the files of workers in difficulty, promoted the normalization of the work of filing, and for workers in difficulty who meet the conditions for filing, they are promptly integrated into the assistance system.
During the epidemic period, it was difficult for migrant workers to go out to work. In order to help ease the living pressure of workers in difficulty at the national level, Yunnan Province arranged more than 13 million yuan in warm relief funds, and implemented special warm relief activities for more than 6,000 families at the national level and more than 1,000 families at the provincial level, in accordance with the standards of 2,000 yuan per family of workers in difficulty at the national level and 1,500 yuan per family of workers in difficulty at the provincial level.
At the same time, the General Administration of the Province has connected with various Internet recruitment platforms, such as the Department of Human and Social Affairs and the Intellectual Recruitment Union, to push recruitment information to workers in difficulty, and to provide employment counselling, employment guidance and other services.
